{
  "stem": "23428.2",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But these were-- these were the really-- at the time in Hungary, it was when the government was run by rabid fascists.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I mean, even more rabid probably than much of what had happened in Germany.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "So anyway, so that was Uncle Fritz.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "He was also, as I say, I mean, he was very rich from his wife, but also extremely stingy.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "So he never helped us, I don't think.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And I remember my father complaining always when they took the tramway together that he had to pay the tram fare for my rich uncle because he never had-- you know, all of his money was in stocks.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "He would never part with anything.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "So this was a rather curious relationship.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And also, you know, just to show you what sort of bastard he really was, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] there was another brother who ended up in America-- we may have to talk to him later-- about him later-- who-- who immigrated to America in 1936, saying that he was a bachelor, because he couldn't otherwise get a visa.",
      "word_count": 59
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "He left his wife and his children in Breslau to perish.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And Father saved both of these kids.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "One of them he sent to Sweden.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "Some Lutheran organization took him in and he ended up as a stable boy in Northern Sweden.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "The other one, the girl, ended up in England with Quakers, also a drama story by herself.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "She's still alive.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So anyway, so when the-- the boy arrived in Budapest when we were living in this one room.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And my father went to his brother, begging him to do something for this kid.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "He could have stayed with us, had we had-- you know, Father couldn't feed our family.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But he never budged a finger.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
